{"key":"processedPost-13208576","value":{"id":13208576,"first":13208461,"last":13208601,"when":1284735185,"utime":"09/17/10 05:53 PM","content":"I'd put it to one side rather than on top.&nbsp; This gets it closer to the substrate, which is where it matters.&nbsp; Disregard bad advice that mushrooms don't need much light.&nbsp; They do.&nbsp; If one is comparing to plants, they don't need as much as growing pot, but they do need bright light to develop to the full finish weight you're looking for.<br />The amount of light received by the mycelium decreases by the square of the distance, so get it as close as possible without excessive heating of the terrarium.&nbsp; Put it on a timer for 12/12.<br />RR","title":"Re: Lighting Question (yes, I've searched already)"}}